  "market_context": "Thursday, 14 Sep 2023, around 10:10–10:12 AM EST. Price had formed equal highs near 15568.75 as draw on liquidity, then swept equal lows before a bullish displacement move.",
  "key_observation": "Price swept equal lows, formed a bullish breaker block (low-high-lower low-higher high), with an overlapping fair value gap used for entry, targeting the prior equal highs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified equal highs near 15568.75 as the draw on liquidity and equal lows below as potential sweep target.",
    "Step 2: Observed price making a new low, forming a low-high-lower low sequence, then a higher high with displacement through the last up-close candle.",
    "Step 3: Marked the bullish breaker block using the highest up-close candle prior to the upward displacement move.",
    "Step 4: Confirmed an overlapping fair value gap where the high of the displacement candle did not overlap the low of the preceding candle.",
    "Step 5: Positioned entry at the fair value gap zone (approx. 15565–15585), with stop below the breaker block low (~15560) or below the FVG (~15565), calculating ~2.3R risk.",
    "Step 6: Noted confluence from standard deviation projection of the manipulation leg targeting the 2–2.5σ area near the equal highs."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade reached the equal highs target (15568.75); frame f010 shows closed P&L of +81.75 with 1 contract, confirming successful execution.",
  "lessons": "The unicorn model (breaker block + overlapping FVG) provides a precise entry zone after a liquidity sweep. Equal highs serve as high-probability draw-on-liquidity targets when paired with structural confirmation and confluence.",
